Copy by ear

Morse Flipper trains sound first. Let your ears learn the letters. Do not start counting in dots and dashes!
---
First drill

From the menu, open Training > Listening. The first lesson is only K and M. Try a few rounds and learn to hear the difference.
---
Key or buttons

The Flipper buttons work. A straight key or paddle works too. Set Input and GPIO before wiring anything clever.
---
No dot counting

Do not learn Morse as dots and dashes. If you are counting, increase spaces between letters, but do not slow the letters down.
---
Practice paths

Listening builds copy by ear. When you are ready to send, Training has timing practice for a straight key, and TX Groups for clean groups under pressure.
---
More tools

Free Practice sends. Ham Keyer and RF are for experiments and radio work. There is more in Help, including wiring notes and practice advice.
